Links

Below are a set of links for you to use during and after the math & stats bootcamp in-class session.

Install instructions for R, Rstudio, and Radiant

Please make sure you have installed, R, Rstudio, and Radiant before the start of the in-class session. Use the install instructions linked below.

https://radiant-rstats.github.io/docs/install.html

Follow along with the install video for your OS in the page linked above and ensure you can start Radiant and you see a page like the image shown below:

Browser

I highly recommend you do not use Internet Explorer as your default browser on Windows. Unless you have a strong preference for Firefox or Safari (macOS) I recommend Chrome which is available for free through the link below:

https://www.google.com/chrome/

Canvas

Check that you can sign into Canvas @ https://canvas.ucsd.edu

Sign up for piazza

MGT 403 will use piazza as a discussion forum. There will be a separate site for each class section: Full-time (FT), Flex-evening (FE), and Flex-weekend (FW). Use the appropriate information for you provided below:

https://piazza.com/ucsd/fall2019/mgt403ft

Download materials

To access materials for the in-class session, run the command below in the Rstudio console (i.e., the bottom-left window)

usethis::use_course("https://www.dropbox.com/sh/6au1158xifevoh9/AADYz5c0gWk9gfbX15lkazWOa?dl=1")

Dropbox

Some professors may choose to share files with you through Dropbox. You can create an account on Dropbox and download the software to install on your computer through the link below:

https://www.dropbox.com/downloading

Radiant documentation

https://radiant-rstats.github.io/docs/

You do not need to know how to program in R to use Radiant. However, if you are interested in learning more about the R programming language for data analysis, the links below are a great place to start:

  • https://www.datacamp.com/courses/free-introduction-to-r
  • https://www.datacamp.com/courses/introduction-to-the-tidyverse
  • https://radiant-rstats.github.io/docs/programming.html
